snippet.textDisplay: There are so many plot holes in this film. The Knights Of REN were absolutely useless, and they were used extensively in trailers, flashbacks, etc. Poe acting was cringe. The movie moved at such a breakneck pace with literally no time for exposition. You’re completely right, the Last Jedi fucked up so much that the 9th film had to correct so much that it took away from what COULD have been a good trilogy.  The Force Awakens wasn’t great, but I felt it was leading into something that could have been great. Ending with Rey killing Palpatine the way she did was lame as hell. Rumors have it that they had Anakin force Ghost along with many others in the film but it was cut. Main issue is this: As long as KK has any creative control over cannon films, we are in trouble. Lucas selling to Disney was a deal with the devil from the start. Look at what Filoni and Favreau are doing with Mandalorian. Get good creators behind the work without interference from the corporation and you can get gold.

snippet.textDisplay:
It seems like the idea they introduced in this film that all the Jedi are in Rey and all the Sith are in Palpatine explains the reason for Rey’s strength rather than the fact that she’s a Palpatine. The force is more concentrated when there are fewer force users. Thus she was way stronger. Especially why she was strong than Kylo because there were two Sith while there was only one jedi alive. That we know of.

Also, would just like to point out that Kylo completed Anakin’s arc by saving the one he loved. Anakin could never do it because he was not ready to lose his own life. On top of that, I think Rey could claim Skywalker more like she’s married into it. She’s basically Padme. Had Anakin been willing to sacrifice himself, the skywalker name would have been carried through Padme, though she’s originally an Amidala.
